parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: To dare, endure, be bold, have courage, make up the mind. From tolma; to venture; by implication, to be courageous.
A prolonged form of an otherwise obsolete verb; to talk, i.e. Utter words.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Accusative Neuter Singular
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Genitive Neuter Plural

str2: Anointed One; the Messiah, the Christ. From chrio; Anointed One, i.e. The Messiah, an epithet of Jesus.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From kata and ergazomai; to work fully, i.e. Accomplish; by implication, to finish, fashion.
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Probably from etho; a race, i.e. A tribe; specially, a foreign one.
Obedience, submissiveness, compliance. From hupakouo; attentive hearkening, i.e. compliance or submission.
From lego; something said; by implication, a topic, also reasoning or motive; by extension, a computation; specially, the Divine Expression.
From a primary ergo; toil; by implication, an act.
